<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TolE0355">
<l>muṉṉeṉ kiḷavi muṉṉart tōṉṟu</l>
<l>milleṉ kiḷavimicai ṟakara moṟṟa</l>
<l>ṟolliyaṉ maruṅkiṉ marīiya marapē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>It is the traditional way of ' deformed ' usage</l>
<l>that the sound <foreign xml:lang="ta">ṟ</foreign> is inserted with the word <foreign xml:lang="ta">il</foreign></l>
<l>when preceded by the word <foreign xml:lang="ta">muṉ.</foreign><note place="foot">e.g. <foreign xml:lang="ta">muṉ</foreign> ' front ' + <foreign xml:lang="ta">il</foreign> ' house ' &gt; <foreign xml:lang="ta">muṉṟil</foreign> '
          courtyard '. The aphorism specifically states that this is a <foreign xml:lang="ta">marūu,</foreign>
          a ' deformed ', ' corrupt ' or contracted form sanctioned by usage ; obviously an old form
          not conforming to the norm and the rules.</note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
